<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-07T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-07T09:00:00-05:00" n="940" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d940">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867.5151/160: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-07T16:00:00+02:00">December 7, 1939—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 7—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>154. My telegram No. 149, November 25, 2 p.m. Exchange transfers have
                                been effected on all applications filed prior to March 10. Unpaid
                                applications on file on December 4 total $6,300,000. Total payments
                                made on applications filed in 1939 (not including payments to
                                petroleum companies) amount to $1,216,000.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>